ServerPackage.ServerControllers

Interface SCCommunicationConstants

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ShopController

    public interface SCCommunicationConstants
    Contains constant String variables for server-client message communication. Messages take the format of: Opening ArgDegree ArgType ArgExtra Messages are from the perspective of the server.
    Since:
    April 1, 2019
    Version:
    2.0
    Author:
    Jake Liu, Shamez Meghji, Victor Sanchez

    • Field Summary

      • scUpdate

        static final java.lang.String scUpdate
        String message Opening, that indicates that data in the reader will change, and new data may or may not be added. If necessary, data will overwrite data in the reader if data with the same identity attributes exists.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • scCreate

        static final java.lang.String scCreate
        String message Opening, that indicates that data will be received from the socket. New data will be created in the reader based on the received data.
